cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with image processing and specifically focuses on single-image superresolution of remotely sensed data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves mathematical justification and sparse representations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of directional features and edge detection further suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
